      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Tristram Gilman (1735-1809) was the pastor of the First Congregational Church of North Yarmouth, Maine, from 1769-1807. A native of 
	  New Hampshire and a graduate of Harvard College in 1757, Gilman is noted for religious revivals instituted in 1791 which resulted 
	  in a wave of religious interest throughout New England.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Tristram Gilman Sermons</emph> consists of a collection of 30 sermons, handwritten, bound in a single volume.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
